###

## Mailbox Access Scope Restrictions 

## To scope an azure graph application to a specific 365 mailbox you cannot scope graph permissionsions in azure, you have to define a scope pointed to the specific mailbox in exchange online, then use a service principal pointer to bridge exchange online to the graph application. Finally, use a management role assignment in exchange online to connect the graph pointer to the mailbox scope. 

# Replace with the actual email address of the target mailbox
New-ManagementScope -Name "Single-Mailbox-Scope" -RecipientRestrictionFilter "PrimarySmtpAddress -eq 'target-mailbox@yourdomain.com'"



# OR 
# Alternative approach using theUserPrincipalName

New-ManagementScope -Name "Single-Mailbox-Scope" -RecipientRestrictionFilter "UserPrincipalName -eq 'target-mailbox@yourdomain.com'"

# Create a Service Principal Pointer in Exchange Online
# You need to find your service principal's Object ID (not the Application ID) from Entra ID. This is the "object ID" of the ENTERPRISE APPLICATION SERVICE PRINCIPAL, and NOT the object ID of the APP REGISTRATION. This step creates a pointer to the specific instance of an app

New-ServicePrincipal -AppId "YOUR-CLIENT-ID (this is the application client ID in Azure" -ObjectId "YOUR-SERVICE-PRINCIPAL-OBJECT-ID" -DisplayName "Your-App-Name (can be anything, I prefer to make this the name of the azure App Registration"

# For mail access (replace with the appropriate role based on your needs)
# Note: Cannot add multiple roles in one line, for each role (mail.read, mail.write etc) you must rerun the command with the new role. 
New-ManagementRoleAssignment -App "SERVICEPRINCIPAL APP DISPLAYNAME (Displayname )" -Role "Application Mail.Read" -CustomResourceScope "Single-Mailbox-Scope"

Example of comman application Roles:

Application Mail.Read - Read email only
Application Mail.ReadWrite - Read and manage email (no send)
Application Mail.Send - Send mail


###
New-ManagementScope -Name "SRT_Reporting_Mailbox" -RecipientRestrictionFilter "PrimarySmtpAddress -eq 'srtreporting@arrowmarkpartners.com'"

